#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:136
#, no-c-format
msgid "Preparing the Virtual Machine"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:138
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If running <command>virt-v2v</command> on &slsa; 12 SP1 or before, this step "
"can be safely skipped. This step can also be ignored if the virtual machine "
"is fully virtualized or if it runs a &slsa; 12 SP2 or later."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:145
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The &xen; virtual machine must have default kernel installed. To ensure "
"this, run <command>zypper in kernel-default</command> in the virtual machine."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:153
#, no-c-format
msgid "Converting Virtual Machines to Run under &kvm; Managed by &libvirt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:155
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>virt-v2v</command> converts virtual machines from the &xen; "
"hypervisor to run under &kvm; managed by &libvirt;. To learn more about "
"&libvirt; and <command>virsh</command>, see <xref linkend=\"part.virt.libvirt"
"\"/>. Additionally, all <command>virt-v2v</command> command line options are "
"explained in the <command>virt-v2v</command> manual page (<command>man 1 "
"virt-v2v</command>)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:164
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Before converting a virtual machine, make sure to complete the following "
"steps:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:169
#, no-c-format
msgid "Preparing the Environment for the Conversion"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:171
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create a new local storage pool."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:174
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>virt-v2v</command> copies the storage of the source virtual machine "
"to a local storage pool managed by &libvirt; (the original disk image "
"remains unchanged). You can create the pool either with &vmm;, or "
"<command>virsh</command>. For more information, see <xref linkend=\"sec."
"libvirt.storage.vmm\"/> and <xref linkend=\"sec.libvirt.storage.virsh\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:184
#, no-c-format
msgid "Prepare the local network interface."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:187
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Check that the converted virtual machine can use a local network interface "
"on the &vmhost;. It is usually a network bridge. If it is not defined yet, "
"create it with <menuchoice><guimenu>&yast;</guimenu><guimenu>System</"
"guimenu><guimenu>Network Settings</guimenu><guimenu>Add</"
"guimenu><guimenu>Bridge</guimenu></menuchoice>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:195
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Network devices on the source &xen; host can be mapped during the conversion "
"process to corresponding network devices on the &kvm; target host (for "
"example, the &xen; bridge <literal>br0</literal> can be mapped to the KVM "
"network default). Sample mappings can be found in <filename>/etc/virt-v2v."
"conf</filename>. To enable these mappings, modify the XML rule as necessary "
"and ensure the section is not commented out with <literal>&lt;!--</literal> "
"and <literal>--&gt;</literal> markers. For example:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:205
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;network type='bridge' name='br0'&gt;\n"
"   &lt;network type='network' name='default'/&gt;\n"
" &lt;/network&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:208
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If there is no network bridge available, &vmm; can optionally create it."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:215
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>virt-v2v</command> has the following basic command syntax:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:218
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"virt-v2v -i <replaceable>input_method</replaceable> -os "
"<replaceable>storage_pool</replaceable> <replaceable>source_vm</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:221
#, no-c-format
msgid "input_method"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:223
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are two input methods: <literal>libvirt</literal> or "
"<literal>libvirtxml</literal>. See the <replaceable>source_vm</replaceable> "
"parameter for more information."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:231
#, no-c-format
msgid "storage_pool"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:233
#, no-c-format
msgid "The storage pool you already prepared for the target virtual machine."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:239
#, no-c-format
msgid "source_vm"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:241
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The source virtual machine to convert. It depends on the "
"<replaceable>input_method</replaceable> parameter: for <literal>libvirt</"
"literal>, specify the name of a libvirt domain, while for "
"<literal>libvirtxml</literal>, specify the path to an XML file containing a "
"libvirt domain specification."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:252
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Conversion of a virtual machine takes a lot of system resources, mainly for "
"copying the whole disk image for a virtual machine. Converting a single "
"virtual machine typically takes up to 10 minutes, although virtual machines "
"using very large disk images can take much longer."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:260
#, no-c-format
msgid "Conversion Based on the &libvirt; XML Description File"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:261
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This section describes how to convert a local &xen; virtual machine using "
"the &libvirt; XML configuration file. This method is suitable if the host is "
"already running the &kvm; hypervisor. Make sure that the &libvirt; XML file "
"of the source virtual machine and the &libvirt; storage pool referenced from "
"it, are available on the local host."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:271
#, no-c-format
msgid "Obtain the &libvirt; XML description of the source virtual machine."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:276
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To obtain the &libvirt; XML files of the source virtual machine, you must "
"run the host OS under the &xen; kernel. If you already rebooted the host to "
"the &kvm;-enabled environment, reboot back to the &xen; kernel, dump the "
"&libvirt; XML file, and then reboot back to the &kvm; environment."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:284
#, no-c-format
msgid "First identify the source virtual machine under virsh:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:287 xen2kvm_quick.xml:367
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;virsh list\n"
" Id    Name                           State\n"
"----------------------------------------------------\n"
"[...]\n"
"  2     sles12_xen                     running\n"
"[...]"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:288
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>sles12_xen</literal> is the source virtual machine to convert. Now "
"export its XML and save it to <filename>sles12_xen.xml</filename>:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:293
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;virsh dumpxml sles12_xen &gt; sles12_xen.xml"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:296
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Verify all disk image paths are correct from the &kvm; host's perspective. "
"This is not a problem when converting on one machine, but may require manual "
"changes when converting using a XML dump from another host."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:302
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;source file='/var/lib/libvirt/images/XenPool/SLES.qcow2'/&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:304
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To avoid copying an image twice, manually copy the disk image(s) directly to "
"the &libvirt; storage pool and update source file entries in the XML "
"description file. The <command>virt-v2v</command> process will detect the "
"existing disks and convert them in place."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:313 xen2kvm_quick.xml:374
#, no-c-format
msgid "Run <command>virt-v2v</command> to convert to &kvm; virtual machine:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:317
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;virt-v2v sles12_xen.xml<co xml:id=\"v2v.xml\"/> \\\n"
"-i <replaceable>libvirtxml</replaceable><co xml:id=\"v2v.method\"/> \\\n"
"-os <replaceable>remote_host.example.com:/exported_dir</replaceable><co xml:"
"id=\"v2v.pool\"/> \\\n"
"--bridge <replaceable>br0</replaceable><co xml:id=\"v2v.bridge\"/> \\\n"
"-on <replaceable>sles12_kvm</replaceable><co xml:id=\"v2v.name\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:320
#, no-c-format
msgid "The XML description of the source &xen;-based virtual machine."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:325
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>virt-v2v</command> will read the information about the source "
"virtual machine form a &libvirt; XML file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:331
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Storage pool where the target virtual machine disk image will be placed. In "
"this example, the image will be placed on an NFS share <filename>/"
"exported_dir</filename> on the <literal>remote_host.example.com</literal> "
"server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:339
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The target &kvm;-based virtual machine will use the network bridge "
"<literal>br0</literal> on the host."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:345
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The target virtual machine will be renamed to <literal>sles12_kvm</literal> "
"to prevent name collision with the existing virtual machine of the same name."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:356
#, no-c-format
msgid "Conversion Based on the &libvirt; Domain Name"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:357
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This method is useful if you are still running &libvirt; under &xen;, and "
"plan to reboot to the &kvm; hypervisor later."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:363
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Find the &libvirt; domain name of the virtual machine you want to convert."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:368 xen2kvm_quick.xml:460
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>sles12_xen</literal> is the source virtual machine to convert."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:378
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;virt-v2v sles12_xen<co xml:id=\"v2v.domain\"/> \\\n"
"-i <replaceable>libvirt</replaceable><co xml:id=\"v2v.method1\"/> \\\n"
"-os <replaceable>storage_pool</replaceable><co xml:id=\"v2v.pool1\"/> \\\n"
"--network <replaceable>eth0</replaceable><co xml:id=\"v2v.net\"/> \\\n"
"-of qcow2<co xml:id=\"v2v.qcow\"/> \\\n"
"-oa sparce<co xml:id=\"v2v.sparse\"/> \\\n"
"-on <replaceable>sles12_kvm</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:381
#, no-c-format
msgid "The domain name of the &xen;-based virtual machine."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:386
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>virt-v2v</command> will read the information about the source "
"virtual machine directly from the active &libvirt; connection."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:393
#, no-c-format
msgid "The target disk image will be placed in a local &libvirt; storage pool."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:399
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"All guest bridges (or networks) will be connected to a locally managed "
"network."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:405
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Format for the disk image of the target virtual machine. Supported options "
"are <option>raw</option> or <option>qcow2</option>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:411
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the converted guest disk space will be <option>sparse</option> or "
"<option>preallocated</option>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:421
#, no-c-format
msgid "Converting a Remote &xen; Virtual Machine"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:422
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This method is useful if you need to convert a &xen; virtual machine running "
"on a remote host. As <command>virt-v2v</command> connects to the remote host "
"via <command>ssh</command>, ensure that SSH service is running on the host."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:430
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Since &slsa; 12 SP2 <command>virt-v2v</command> requires a password-less SSH "
"connection to the remote host. This means a connection using an SSH key "
"added to the ssh-agent. See <command>man ssh-keygen</command> and "
"<command>man ssh-add</command> for more details on this."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:439
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To connect to a remote &libvirt; connection, construct a valid connection "
"URI relevant for your remote host. In the following example, the remote host "
"name is <literal>remote_host.example.com</literal>, and the username for the "
"connection is &rootuser;. The connection URI then looks as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:446
#, no-c-format
msgid "xen+ssh://root@remote_host.example.com/"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:448
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For more information on &libvirt; connection URIs, see <link xlink:href="
"\"http://libvirt.org/uri.html\"></link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:455
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Find the &libvirt; domain name of the remote virtual machine you want to "
"convert."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:459
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;virsh -c xen+ssh://root@remote_host.example.com/ list\n"
" Id    Name                           State\n"
"----------------------------------------------------\n"
"  1     sles12_xen                     running\n"
"[...]"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:466
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <command>virt-v2v</command> command for the remote connection looks like "
"this:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:470
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;virt-v2v sles12_xen \\\n"
"-i <replaceable>libvirt</replaceable> \\\n"
"-ic <replaceable>xen+ssh://root@remote_host.example.com/</replaceable> \\\n"
"-os <replaceable>local_storage_pool</replaceable> \\\n"
"--bridge <replaceable>br0</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:477
#, no-c-format
msgid "Running Converted Virtual Machines"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:478
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After <command>virt-v2v</command> completes successfully, a new &libvirt; "
"domain will be created with the name specified with the <option>-on</option> "
"option. If you did not specify <option>-on</option>, the same name as the "
"source virtual machine will be used. The new guest can be managed with "
"standard &libvirt; tools, such as <command>virsh</command> or &vmm;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:487
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You may need to reboot the host machine and boot with the non-&xen; kernel "
"if you just completed the conversion under &xen; as in the case of <xref "
"linkend=\"x2k.v2v.convert.domain\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:496
#, no-c-format
msgid "&xen; to &kvm; Manual Migration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:501
#, no-c-format
msgid "General Outline"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:502
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The preferred solution to manage virtual machines is based on &libvirt;; for "
"more information, see <link xlink:href=\"http://libvirt.org/\"></link>. It "
"has several advantages over the manual way of defining and running virtual "
"machines&mdash;&libvirt; is cross-platform, supports many hypervisors, "
"secure remote management, virtual networking, and, most of all, provides a "
"unified abstract layer to manage virtual machines. Therefore the main focus "
"of this article is on the &libvirt; solution."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:512
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Generally, the &xen; to &kvm; migration runs in the following basic steps:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:518
#, no-c-format
msgid "Make a backup copy of the original &xen; &vmguest;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:523
#, no-c-format
msgid "OPTIONAL: Apply changes specific to paravirtualized guests."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:528
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Obtain information about the original &xen; &vmguest; and update it to &kvm; "
"equivalents."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:534
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Shut down the guest on the &xen; host, and run the new one under the &kvm; "
"hypervisor."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:541
#, no-c-format
msgid "No Live Migration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:542
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The &xen; to &kvm; migration cannot be done live while the source &vmguest; "
"is running. Before running the new &kvm;-ready &vmguest;, you are advised to "
"shut down the original &xen; &vmguest;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:552
#, no-c-format
msgid "Back Up the &xen; &vmguest;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:553
#, no-c-format
msgid "To back up your &xen; &vmguest;, follow these steps:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:558
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Identify the relevant &xen; guest you want to migrate, and remember its ID/"
"name."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:562
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"# virsh list --all\n"
"Id Name                 State\n"
"----------------------------------\n"
" 0 Domain-0             running\n"
" 1 SLES11SP3            running\n"
"[...]"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:565
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Shut down the guest. You can do this either by shutting down the guest OS, "
"or with <command>virsh</command>:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:569
