#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:595
#, no-c-format
msgid "Changes Specific to Paravirtualized Guests"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:596
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Apply the following changes if you are migrating a paravirtualized &xen; "
"guest. You can do it either on the running guest, or on the stopped guest "
"using <literal>guestfs-tools</literal>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:603
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After applying the changes described in this section, the image file related "
"to the migrated &vmguest; will not be usable under &xen; anymore."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:610
#, no-c-format
msgid "Install the Default Kernel"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:612
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After you install the default kernel, do not try to boot the &xen; guest "
"with it, the system will not boot."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:617
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Before cloning the &xen; guest disk image for use under the &kvm; "
"hypervisor, make sure it is bootable <emphasis>without</emphasis> the &xen; "
"hypervisor. This is very important for paravirtualized &xen; guests as they "
"usually contain a special &xen; kernel, and often do not have a complete "
"&grub; boot loader installed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:626
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For &slsa; 11 update the <filename>/etc/sysconfig/kernel</filename> file. "
"Change the <literal>INITRD_MODULES</literal> parameter by removing all &xen; "
"drivers and replacing the with virtio drivers. Replace"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:632
#, no-c-format
msgid "INITRD_MODULES=\"xenblk xennet\""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:633 xen2kvm_quick.xml:717
#, no-c-format
msgid "with"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:636
#, no-c-format
msgid "INITRD_MODULES=\"virtio_blk virtio_pci virtio_net virtio_balloon\""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:637
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For &slsa; 12 search for <literal>xenblk xennet</literal> in <filename>/etc/"
"dracut.conf.d/*.conf</filename> and replace them with <literal>virtio_blk "
"virtio_pci virtio_net virtio_balloon</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:643
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Paravirtualized &xen; guests are running a specific &xen; kernel. To run the "
"guest under &kvm;, you need to install the default kernel."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:649
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You do not need to install the default kernel for a fully virtualized guests "
"as it is already installed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:654
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Enter <command>rpm -q kernel-default</command> on the &xen; guest to find "
"out if the default kernel is installed. If not, install it with "
"<command>zypper in kernel-default</command>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:659
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The kernel we are going to use to boot the guest under &kvm; must have "
"<emphasis>virtio</emphasis> (paravirtualized) drivers available. Run the "
"following command to find out. Do not forget to replace <literal>3.8.9-4</"
"literal> with your kernel version:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:665
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"# find /lib/modules/3.8.9-4-default/kernel/drivers/ -name virtio*\n"
"/lib/modules/3.8.9-4-default/kernel/drivers/net/virtio_net.ko\n"
"/lib/modules/3.8.9-4-default/kernel/drivers/scsi/virtio_scsi.ko\n"
"/lib/modules/3.8.9-4-default/kernel/drivers/block/virtio_blk.ko\n"
"/lib/modules/3.8.9-4-default/kernel/drivers/char/virtio_console.ko\n"
"/lib/modules/3.8.9-4-default/kernel/drivers/char/hw_random/virtio-rng.ko\n"
"/lib/modules/3.8.9-4-default/kernel/drivers/virtio\n"
"/lib/modules/3.8.9-4-default/kernel/drivers/virtio/virtio.ko\n"
"/lib/modules/3.8.9-4-default/kernel/drivers/virtio/virtio_pci.ko\n"
"/lib/modules/3.8.9-4-default/kernel/drivers/virtio/virtio_balloon.ko\n"
"/lib/modules/3.8.9-4-default/kernel/drivers/virtio/virtio_ring.ko\n"
"/lib/modules/3.8.9-4-default/kernel/drivers/virtio/virtio_mmio.ko"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:668
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Update <filename>/etc/fstab</filename>. Change any storage devices from "
"<literal>xvda</literal> to <literal>vda</literal>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:674
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Update the boot loader configuration. Enter <command>rpm -q grub2</command> "
"on the &xen; guest to find out if &grub; is already installed. If not, "
"install it with <command>zypper in grub2</command>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:680
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Now make the newly installed default kernel the default for booting the OS. "
"Also remove/update the kernel command line options that may refer to &xen;-"
"specific devices. You can do it either with &yast; "
"(<menuchoice><guimenu>System</guimenu><guimenu>Boot Loader</guimenu></"
"menuchoice>), or manually:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:689
#, no-c-format
msgid "Find the preferred Linux boot menu entry by listing them all:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:692
#, no-c-format
msgid "cat /boot/grub2/grub.cfg | grep 'menuentry '"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:693
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Remember the order number (counted from zero) of the one you newly installed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:699
#, no-c-format
msgid "Set it the default boot menu entry:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:702
#, no-c-format
msgid "grub2-set-default <replaceable>N</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:703
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Replace <replaceable>N</replaceable> with the number of the boot menu entry "
"you previously discovered."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:709
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Open <filename>/etc/default/grub</filename>for editing, and look for "
"<option>GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_DEFAULT</option> and "
"<option>GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_RECOVERY</option> options. Remove/update any "
"reference to &xen;-specific devices. In the following example, you can "
"replace"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:716
#, no-c-format
msgid "root=/dev/xvda1 disk=/dev/xvda console=xvc"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:720
#, no-c-format
msgid "root=/dev/vda1 disk=/dev/vda"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:721
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note that you need to remove all references to <literal>xvc</literal>-type "
"consoles (such as <literal>xvc0</literal>)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:730
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Update <filename>device.map</filename> in one of <filename>/boot/grub2</"
"filename> or <filename>/boot/grub2-efi</filename> directories. Change any "
"storage device from <literal>xvda</literal> to <literal>vda</literal>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:738
#, no-c-format
msgid "To import new default settings, run"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:741
#, no-c-format
msgid "grub2-mkconfig -o /boot/grub2/grub.cfg"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:746
#, no-c-format
msgid "Update the Guest for Boot under &kvm;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:749
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Update the system to use default serial console. List the configured "
"consoles, and remove symbolic links to <literal>xvc?</literal> ones."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:753
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"# ls -l /etc/systemd/system/getty.target.wants/\n"
"getty@tty1.service -&gt; /usr/lib/systemd/system/getty@.service\n"
"getty@xvc0.service -&gt; /usr/lib/systemd/system/getty@xvc0.service\n"
"getty@xvc1.service -&gt; /usr/lib/systemd/system/getty@xvc1.service\n"
"\n"
"# rm /etc/systemd/system/getty.target.wants/getty@xvc?.service"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:756
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Update the <filename>/etc/securetty</filename> file. Replace <literal>xvc0</"
"literal> with <literal>ttyS0</literal>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:766
#, no-c-format
msgid "Update the &xen; &vmguest; Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:767
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This section describes how to export the configuration of the original &xen; "
"&vmguest;, and what particular changes to apply to it to be able to import "
"it as a &kvm; guest into &libvirt;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:773
#, no-c-format
msgid "Export the &xen; &vmguest; Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:774
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"First export the configuration of the guest and save it to a file. A typical "
"one may look like this:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen2kvm_quick.xml:778
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"# virsh dumpxml SLES11SP3\n"
